Bug.WithStack:
As it has been discussed in the newsgroup, it may be required to check the cvs
server version.
Here is some code the does it (in the
src/org/eclipse/team/internal/ccvs/core/client/Session.java file of
org.eclipse.team.cvs.core plugin). I wrote it against revision 1.17 of the file.
While the code is probably badly written (and does not use the appropriate class
hierarchy)
but you can get the idea.
(it works and can save some trouble from people using incompatible versions of
cvs servers).
(the checkCVSVersion method is called right after opening the cvs connection).

Genady

